# Git / deploy workflow

Both apps (Tasks App and Lawn Care App) should always be committed and pushed together using the shared script at `C:\Projects\push-all.ps1`.

## Committing via the agent

When the user says "commit", "push", "deploy", or similar, run:

```powershell
C:\Projects\push-all.ps1 "commit message here"
```

This stages all changes, commits, and pushes **both repos** in one command.

## Committing manually (terminal)

The user can open a terminal and run:

```powershell
C:\Projects\push-all.ps1 "describe what changed"
```

## Notes

- Always push to `main` (Tasks App) / `master` (Lawn Care App) — never create branches unless explicitly asked.
- If only one repo has changes the script skips the other automatically.
